 266:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c **** /** @defgroup UARTEx_Exported_Functions_Group3 Peripheral Control functions
 267:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   * @brief    Extended Peripheral Control functions
 268:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   *
 269:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c **** @verbatim
 270:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****  ===============================================================================
 271:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****                       ##### Peripheral Control functions #####
 272:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****  ===============================================================================
 273:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****     [..] This section provides the following functions:
 274:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****      (+) HAL_UARTEx_EnableClockStopMode() API enables the UART clock (HSI or LSE only) during stop 
 275:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****      (+) HAL_UARTEx_DisableClockStopMode() API disables the above functionality
 276:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****      (+) HAL_MultiProcessorEx_AddressLength_Set() API optionally sets the UART node address
 277:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****          detection length to more than 4 bits for multiprocessor address mark wake up.
 278:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****      (+) HAL_UARTEx_StopModeWakeUpSourceConfig() API defines the wake-up from stop mode
 279:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****          trigger: address match, Start Bit detection or RXNE bit status.
 280:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****      (+) HAL_UARTEx_EnableStopMode() API enables the UART to wake up the MCU from stop mode
 281:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****      (+) HAL_UARTEx_DisableStopMode() API disables the above functionality
 282:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c **** 
 283:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****     [..] This subsection also provides a set of additional functions providing enhanced reception
 284:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****     services to user. (For example, these functions allow application to handle use cases
 285:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****     where number of data to be received is unknown).
 286:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c **** 
 287:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****     (#) Compared to standard reception services which only consider number of received
 288:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****         data elements as reception completion criteria, these functions also consider additional ev
 289:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****         as triggers for updating reception status to caller :
 290:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****        (++) Detection of inactivity period (RX line has not been active for a given period).
 291:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****           (+++) RX inactivity detected by IDLE event, i.e. RX line has been in idle state (normally
 292:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****                for 1 frame time, after last received byte.
 293:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****           (+++) RX inactivity detected by RTO, i.e. line has been in idle state
 294:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****                for a programmable time, after last received byte.
 295:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****        (++) Detection that a specific character has been received.
 296:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c **** 
 297:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****     (#) There are two modes of transfer:
 298:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****        (++) Blocking mode: The reception is performed in polling mode, until either expected number
 299:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****            or till IDLE event occurs. Reception is handled only during function execution.
 300:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****            When function exits, no data reception could occur. HAL status and number of actually re
 301:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****            are returned by function after finishing transfer.
 302:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****        (++) Non-Blocking mode: The reception is performed using Interrupts or DMA.
 303:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****            These API's return the HAL status.
 304:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****            The end of the data processing will be indicated through the
 305:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****            dedicated UART IRQ when using Interrupt mode or the DMA IRQ when using DMA mode.
 306:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****            The HAL_UARTEx_RxEventCallback() user callback will be executed during Receive process
 307:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****            The HAL_UART_ErrorCallback()user callback will be executed when a reception error is det
 308:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c **** 
 309:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****     (#) Blocking mode API:
 310:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****         (++) HAL_UARTEx_ReceiveToIdle()
 311:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c **** 
 312:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****     (#) Non-Blocking mode API with Interrupt:
 313:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****         (++) HAL_UARTEx_ReceiveToIdle_IT()
 314:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c **** 
 315:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****     (#) Non-Blocking mode API with DMA:
 316:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****         (++) HAL_UARTEx_ReceiveToIdle_DMA()
 317:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart_ex.c **** 
